did.head: DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY
did.repository: Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library
did.abstract: Includes material related to beekeeping, his membership in the Empire State Honey Producers' Association, and Morse's career in the Dept. of Entomology.

bioghist.head: BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE
bioghist.p: Morse was a bee biologist in the Dept. of Entomology. He received his B.A. in 1950, his master's degree in 1953, and his PhD in 1955, all from Cornell.

scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: Includes correspondence, course material and photographs related to beekeeping, his membership in the Empire State Honey Producers' Association, and Morse's career in the Dept. of Entomology. Also included is a bound volume titled "Burma and Nepal programs and reports," consisting of typewritten documents and correspondence concerning projects that Morse was involved with there. Its spine title is Morse--Asian journey--1982.)
